'''Aayaase''' (also known as '''ᐋᔾᔮᐦᔥ''' ('''Aayaash'''; unpointed as '''ᐊᔾᔭᔥ''') or '''Iyash'''; recorded by [[William Jones (anthropologist)|William Jones]] as '''Āyāsä''')<ref>Jones, William (1917-19). ''Ojibwa Texts'', vol. ii. Truman Michelson, ed. Leyden, New York: G. E. Stechert & co., pp. 380-393</ref> is a character found in the ''[[Aadizookaan]]'' of the [[Anishinaabe]] peoples. Similar in nature to the [[Ojibwa]] [[Nanabozho]] stories, the Aayaash stories tell of his trials and tribulations, with each story carrying a moral.
